}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 141-145.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   Having walked through the smoke, they have now reached its 'edge,' and so \softline
may soon regain the light of the sun.  Thus we learn that Marco and his colleagues in repenting \softline
Wrath all must measure their pace so as not to walk either too slowly or too quickly in the smoke, \softline
which is moving clockwise along the terrace.  The smoke does not come upon them, as it did \softline
Dante and Virgil; they inhabit it.  Marco now retreats from the light, having walked too quickly in \softline
order to keep pace with his new companions.\par
